      purpose:
        'Before placing a single wire on a breadboard, you need to be able to read the schematic and identify every node, net name, and power rail. A node is any point where two or more component leads connect. Net names like VCC and GND label recurring power references. Tracing the current path from power source through each component to ground ensures you understand the circuit intent — which is exactly what you will replicate on the breadboard.',
