        purpose:
          'Watch out for split-rail breadboards. Many full-size breadboards have a physical gap in the power rail at the midpoint, meaning the top half and bottom half of each rail are not connected by default. You must add a jumper wire to bridge this gap, or components on the far side of the board will have no power or ground connection.',
