          'A practical technique: before inserting any polarity-sensitive component, hold it next to the breadboard and point at each lead while saying the pin name out loud — anode then cathode for an LED, base then collector then emitter for a transistor. This verbal check takes two seconds and catches orientation errors before they become hardware failures.',
